From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 16:05:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Classify DualSense speaker sinks before haptic
 targets.

DualSense Edge exposes the controller speaker sink with raw haptic target
metadata. The previous speaker test rejected any sink with raw_haptic_target,
so the Edge speaker did not receive the stable DualSense mono endpoint id and
Spider-Man Remastered saw a different app-facing endpoint after switching from
a standard DualSense to a DualSense Edge.

Treat Pulse `Speaker__sink` devices as the mono speaker endpoint even if they
also carry raw haptic target metadata. Keep the explicit `Direct__Direct__sink`
path classified as the direct haptic sink.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 44444444444..55555555555 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -1203,8 +1203,8 @@ static BOOL is_dualsense_audio_device(const PhysDevice *dev)
 
 static BOOL is_dualsense_speaker_sink(const PhysDevice *dev)
 {
-    return dev->flow == eRender && is_dualsense_audio_device(dev) && !dev->raw_haptic_target
-            && strstr(dev->pulse_name, "Speaker__sink");
+    return dev->flow == eRender && is_dualsense_audio_device(dev)
+            && strstr(dev->pulse_name, "Speaker__sink");
 }
 
 static BOOL pulse_name_looks_like_dualsense_speaker_sink(const char *name)
@@ -2352,8 +2352,8 @@ static char *get_dualsense_speaker_sink(const char *preferred, BOOL require_spea
             if (!is_dualsense_audio_device(dev))
                 continue;
 
-            direct = strstr(dev->pulse_name, "Direct__Direct__sink") || dev->raw_haptic_target;
             speaker = is_dualsense_speaker_sink(dev);
+            direct = strstr(dev->pulse_name, "Direct__Direct__sink") || (dev->raw_haptic_target && !speaker);
             if (require_speaker && !speaker)
                 continue;
 
